isappearance has emerged from within the practice itself and come to be central to its ethos. The result is a sophisticated examination of musical survival and transformation that is also a meditation on temporality, labor, colonialism and nationalism, and the relationship of the living to the dead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aArabszAlgeriavMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aArabszAlgeriaxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aArabszMoroccovMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aArabszMoroccoxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aEthnomusicologyzAfrica, North. 0aMusiczAfrica, NorthxSpanish influences. 0aMusiczAlgeriaxHistory and criticism. 0aMusiczMoroccoxHistory and criticism. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology). 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2014-2016z978311070422808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP eBook-Package 2016z978311068860308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226327372423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226327372.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-068860-3  UChP eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-070422-8  UChP eBook-Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles